#. <section class="sutta" id="sn7.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Arahantavagga"
msgstr "1. The Perfected Ones"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Akkosasutta"
msgstr "2. The Abuser"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.162"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.2:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn7.2:1.2"
msgid "Assosi kho akkosakabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo:"
msgstr "The brahmin Bharadvāja the Rude heard a rumor to the effect that:"

#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.348"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.2:2.1"
msgid ""
"“bhāradvājagotto kira brāhmaṇo samaṇassa gotamassa santike agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajito”ti kupito anattamano yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ asabbhāhi pharusāhi vācāhi akkosati paribhāsati. "
"Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā akkosakabhāradvājaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"“A brahmin of the Bharadvāja clan has gone forth from the lay life to "
"homelessness in the presence of the ascetic Gotama!” Angry and displeased he "
"went to the Buddha and abused and insulted him with rude, harsh words. When "
"he had spoken, the Buddha said to him:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.2:2.2"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa, "
msgstr "“What do you think, brahmin? "

#. VAR: atithiyo → atithayo (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn7.2:2.3"
msgid "api nu kho te āgacchanti mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā atithiyo”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Do friends and colleagues, relatives and family members, and guests still "
"come to visit you?”"

msgctxt "sn7.2:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Appekadā me, bho gotama, āgacchanti mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā atithiyo”ti."
msgstr "“Sometimes they do, Master Gotama.”"

msgctxt "sn7.2:2.5"
msgid ""
"“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa, api nu tesaṃ anuppadesi khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ "
"vā sāyanīyaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you then serve them with a variety of foods and savories?”"

msgctxt "sn7.2:2.6"
msgid ""
"“Appekadā nesāhaṃ, bho gotama, anuppademi khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā "
"sāyanīyaṃ vā”ti."
msgstr "“Sometimes I do.”"

msgctxt "sn7.2:2.7"
msgid "“Sace kho pana te, brāhmaṇa, nappaṭiggaṇhanti, kassa taṃ hotī”ti?"
msgstr "“But if they don’t accept it, brahmin, who does it belong to?”"

msgctxt "sn7.2:2.8"
msgid "“Sace te, bho gotama, nappaṭiggaṇhanti, amhākameva taṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr "“In that case it still belongs to me.”"

msgctxt "sn7.2:2.9"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, yaṃ tvaṃ amhe anakkosante akkosasi, arosente rosesi, "
"abhaṇḍante bhaṇḍasi, taṃ te mayaṃ nappaṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, brahmin, when you abuse, harass, and attack us who do not "
"abuse, harass, and attack, we don’t accept it."

msgctxt "sn7.2:2.10"
msgid "Tavevetaṃ, brāhmaṇa, hoti;"
msgstr "It still belongs to you, brahmin,"

msgctxt "sn7.2:2.11"
msgid "tavevetaṃ, brāhmaṇa, hoti."
msgstr "it still belongs to you!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.2:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, brāhmaṇa, akkosantaṃ paccakkosati, rosentaṃ paṭiroseti, bhaṇḍantaṃ "
"paṭibhaṇḍati, ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, sambhuñjati vītiharatīti."
msgstr ""
"Someone who, when abused, harassed, and attacked, abuses, harasses, and "
"attacks in return is said to eat the food and have a reaction to it."

msgctxt "sn7.2:3.2"
msgid "Te mayaṃ tayā neva sambhuñjāma na vītiharāma."
msgstr "But we neither eat your food nor do we have a reaction to it."

msgctxt "sn7.2:3.3"
msgid "Tavevetaṃ, brāhmaṇa, hoti;"
msgstr "It still belongs to you, brahmin,"

msgctxt "sn7.2:3.4"
msgid "tavevetaṃ, brāhmaṇa, hotī”ti."
msgstr "it still belongs to you!”"

msgctxt "sn7.2:3.5"
msgid "“Bhavantaṃ kho gotamaṃ sarājikā parisā evaṃ jānāti:"
msgstr "“The king and his retinue believe that Master Gotama is"

msgctxt "sn7.2:3.6"
msgid "‘arahaṃ samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "a perfected one."

msgctxt "sn7.2:3.7"
msgid "Atha ca pana bhavaṃ gotamo kujjhatī”ti."
msgstr "And yet he still gets angry.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.349"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.2:4.1"
msgid "“Akkodhassa kuto kodho,"
msgstr "\"For one free of anger, tamed, living in balance,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:4.2"
msgid "dantassa samajīvino;"
msgstr "freed by right knowledge,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:4.3"
msgid "Sammadaññā vimuttassa,"
msgstr "at peace, poised:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:4.4"
msgid "upasantassa tādino."
msgstr "where would anger come from?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.2:5.1"
msgid "Tasseva tena pāpiyo,"
msgstr "When you get angry at an angry person"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:5.2"
msgid "yo kuddhaṃ paṭikujjhati;"
msgstr "you just make things worse for yourself."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:5.3"
msgid "Kuddhaṃ appaṭikujjhanto,"
msgstr "When you don’t get angry at an angry person"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:5.4"
msgid "saṅgāmaṃ jeti dujjayaṃ."
msgstr "you win a battle hard to win."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.2:6.1"
msgid "Ubhinnamatthaṃ carati,"
msgstr "When you know that the other is angry,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:6.2"
msgid "attano ca parassa ca;"
msgstr "you act for the good of both"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:6.3"
msgid "Paraṃ saṅkupitaṃ ñatvā,"
msgstr "yourself and the other"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:6.4"
msgid "yo sato upasammati."
msgstr "if you’re mindful and stay calm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.2:7.1"
msgid "Ubhinnaṃ tikicchantānaṃ,"
msgstr "People unfamiliar with the teaching"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:7.2"
msgid "attano ca parassa ca;"
msgstr "consider one who heals both"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:7.3"
msgid "Janā maññanti bāloti,"
msgstr "oneself and the other"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.2:7.4"
msgid "ye dhammassa akovidā”ti."
msgstr "to be a fool.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.163"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.2:8.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, akkosakabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Bhāradvāja the Rude said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn7.2:8.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …"
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! …"

msgctxt "sn7.2:8.3"
msgid "esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "sn7.2:8.4"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhoto gotamassa santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ "
"upasampadan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.350"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.2:9.1"
msgid ""
"Alattha kho akkosakabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha "
"upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Rude received the going forth, the ordination "
"in the Buddha’s presence."

msgctxt "sn7.2:9.2"
msgid ""
"Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā akkosakabhāradvājo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto "
"ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva "
"dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Not long after his ordination, Venerable Bhāradvāja the Rude, living alone, "
"withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of "
"the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own "
"insight the goal for which people from good families rightly go forth from "
"the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "sn7.2:9.3"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

# No longer “the Rude”! BB’s more abbreviated text conceals this detail.
msgctxt "sn7.2:9.4"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā bhāradvājo arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And Venerable Bhāradvāja became one of the perfected."
